  <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\supportedconfigs.dita" xtrc="title:1;4:10">Beta 1: Supported Configuration</title>
  <body class="- topic/body " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\supportedconfigs.dita" xtrc="body:1;5:9">
    <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\supportedconfigs.dita" xtrc="p:1;6:8">The following list summaries the qualified configurations and their purpose.</p>
    <note class="- topic/note " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\supportedconfigs.dita" xtrc="note:1;7:11">While the hardware requirements are similar to those of HP Helion <tm tmtype="reg" class="- topic/tm " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\supportedconfigs.dita" xtrc="tm:1;8:10">OpenStack</tm> 1.1, this is a completely new installation, not an upgrade or update
      operation.</note>
    <section class="- topic/section " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\supportedconfigs.dita" xtrc="section:1;10:14"><title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\supportedconfigs.dita" xtrc="title:2;10:21">Entry Scale Cloud</title> This is very similar to the Beta0 example but has a
      more complex network configuration. At minimum scale it can be used as a POC (3-4 nodes) but
      can also be scaled up to HP Helion OpenStack 1.1 levels, that is, up to 100 compute nodes. The
      network configuration supports separation of networks for: <ul id="ul_l1v_nbz_2t" class="- topic/ul " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\supportedconfigs.dita" xtrc="ul:1;13:89">
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\supportedconfigs.dita" xtrc="li:1;14:13">Management</li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\supportedconfigs.dita" xtrc="li:2;15:13">External API</li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\supportedconfigs.dita" xtrc="li:3;16:13">External VM communications</li>
      </ul>
      <note class="- topic/note " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\supportedconfigs.dita" xtrc="note:2;18:13"> The requirement to have a dedicated network for OS-install and system deployment has
        been removed in Beta 1. To re-use the deployment network as part of the operational network
        the following conditions must be adhered to:</note>
      <ol id="ol_gdv_nbz_2t" class="- topic/ol " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\supportedconfigs.dita" xtrc="ol:1;21:30">
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\supportedconfigs.dita" xtrc="li:4;22:13">The network IP addresses used for OS install (i.e. baremetalConfig.yml and servers.yml)
          must belong to a Network that is used for your cloud infrastructure (e.g. in
          networks.yml).</li>
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\supportedconfigs.dita" xtrc="li:5;25:13">The Network that re-uses those addresses must be un-tagged.</li>
      </ol> In the example <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\supportedconfigs.dita" xtrc="b:1;26:31">entry-scale model</b> the management network is: <ul id="ul_yfv_nbz_2t" class="- topic/ul " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\supportedconfigs.dita" xtrc="ul:2;27:28">
        <li class="- topic/li " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\supportedconfigs.dita" xtrc="li:6;28:13">Mgmt 10.2.1.0/24 VLAN: 100 (untagged) </li>
      </ul> In the baremetalConfig file servers are listed as:
      <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\supportedconfigs.dita" xtrc="codeblock:1;30:18"> baremetal_servers:
      - node_name: controller1
      node_type: CCN-001-001
      pxe_mac_addr: b2:72:8d:ac:7c:6f
      pxe_interface: eth2
      pxe_ip_addr: 192.168.10.3
      ilo_ip: 192.168.9.3
      </codeblock>
      in the servers.yml file servers will show as:
      <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\supportedconfigs.dita" xtrc="codeblock:2;39:18">- id: controller1
      role: ROLE-CCN
      ip-addr: 192.168.10.3</codeblock> The
      values in the baremetal and servers definition need to members of the CIDR used for the
      untagged network, (in this case Mgmt network). </section>
    <section class="- topic/section " xtrf="C:\Users\sharmabi\git\documentation\helion\supportedconfigs.dita" xtrc="section:2;44:14">Note, the entry-scale cloud model also supports the physical bonding of Network
